<p>In his <a href="https://archive.org/details/tabletalkofwhaud0000anse/page/24/mode/2up"><em>Table Talk</em></a>, W.H. Auden says that La Rochefoucauld &#8220;simply says what one has always known.&#8221;</p>
<p>Robert Craft <a href="https://www.nybooks.com/articles/1991/01/17/uncle-whiz/">added</a>, &#8220;Yes, but without him some of us would not have known that we knew.&#8221;</p>
